From: Claude (devcontainer agent)
Date: 2026-04-27
Subject: [C1, C2, I2, I4, S1, S2, S4, LAT2] post_install.py: round-trip
         escaping, fall-through fix, ordering, error surfacing, helper
         extraction

Why this is a separate patch
============================
This devcontainer mounts /workspace/.devcontainer as read-only inside the
container, so an agent running inside cannot edit post_install.py
directly. Apply this patch from the host (or any environment with write
access to .devcontainer/), then commit and push.

This is a follow-on to the prior round of post_install hardening
(C1-onboarding-bypass, I1-I2-I4-I6-S4) — those patches addressed the
problems known at that time; this patch addresses what the next review
surfaced once those landed and were exercised.

What this fixes
===============

C1 (review 2026-04-27) — `_git_get` round-trip strips git-INI escape/
quote/comment chars
-------------------------------------------------------------------
`git config --file --get` returns the *parsed* value (escapes/quotes
already resolved). The script then re-emitted that value verbatim into
.gitconfig.local with f-strings — `name = {user_name}`. When that file
is later loaded as GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL, git's INI rules re-parse the raw
characters and corrupt the value. Reproduced live (this patch was
verified before submission):

  Host:      [user] name = "Test #1 User"
  _git_get:  Test #1 User
  Re-emit:   name = Test #1 User
  Re-parse:  user.name = "Test " (everything after '#' is comment)

The same truncation hits `;` (j@x;y.com → j@x), and `"`/`\\` get
stripped/duplicated.

The fix introduces `_git_quote_value(value)` which double-quotes the
value and escapes internal `"` and `\\`. Every `name`/`email`/
`signingkey`/`gpgsign` emit goes through it.

C2 (review 2026-04-27) — corrupt-JSON branch falls through to write a
hasCompletedOnboarding stub
--------------------------------------------------------------------
When `claude -p` exits 0 but writes corrupt JSON, the prior version
moved the corrupt file to .bak and *fell through* to the bottom of
setup_onboarding_bypass, writing `{"hasCompletedOnboarding": true}`
to a fresh ~/.claude.json. That's exactly the failure mode the C1
guard at the top of the function (claude -p rc != 0 → return) was
added to prevent — except now the stub overwrites a *just-corrupted*
config rather than a stale-but-valid one. Either way the user sees a
container that claims to be onboarded but has no auth state and
silently fails on next `claude` invocation.

The fix routes through the new `_load_json_or_backup` helper and bails
out unless status == "loaded". The corrupt original (if any) is now at
~/.claude.json.<ts>.bak for the user to recover.

I2 (review 2026-04-27) — setup_claude_settings runs before
fix_directory_ownership, so a root-owned file kills postCreate
-------------------------------------------------------------
Both `setup_onboarding_bypass` and `setup_claude_settings` call
`path.read_text()` before `fix_directory_ownership`. The previous
exception list only caught `JSONDecodeError`, so a `PermissionError`
from a file root-owned by a previous container run would propagate
and abort postCreate before the function designed to chown those
files (`fix_directory_ownership`) even runs. Symptoms: no tmux
config, wrong ownership on /commandhistory and ~/.config/gh, no git
identity.

The fix: move `fix_directory_ownership()` to the FIRST call in
`main()`. Defense-in-depth: `_load_json_or_backup` also catches
`OSError` so a stale or root-owned file produces a clean warning
rather than aborting.

I4 (review 2026-04-27) — `_git_get` swallows malformed-config errors
silently → empty-of-identity container
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Previously, `git config --get` returning rc=1 (key absent) and rc=128
(parse failure) were both treated as "" silently. A malformed host
gitconfig produced a .gitconfig.local with no [user] section, and the
first `git commit` failed with "Author identity unknown" with no
breadcrumb pointing at the parse failure.

The fix: distinguish rc=1 (return "" silently) from rc≠0,1 (warn,
return ""). Additionally, when no identity keys land in
.gitconfig.local at all (key truly absent OR all keys failed to
parse), emit an explicit "no [user] section" warning so the resulting
"Author identity unknown" failure is debuggable.

S1 (review 2026-04-27) — `shutil.move(path, .bak)` silently overwrites
a prior backup
----------------------------------------------------------------------
`path.with_suffix(path.suffix + ".bak")` reuses the same backup name on
every failure, destroying older corrupt state. The fix: timestamp-suffix
each backup with epoch seconds (e.g. `.claude.json.1714225800.bak`) so
each failure keeps its own forensic record.

S2 (review 2026-04-27) — `SMUDGE_DEVCONTAINER_BYPASS` /
`SMUDGE_DEVCONTAINER_INCLUDE_HOST_GITCONFIG` exact-string-match `"1"`
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Previously matched only the literal string "1", so a user who set the
var to `true`, `yes`, or `on` (matching common Linux/Docker conventions
and the rest of the project's env-var style) hit a silent no-op. The
fix: extract `_is_truthy(value)` accepting `{"1", "true", "yes", "on"}`
case-insensitive, whitespace-trimmed.

S4 (review 2026-04-27) — duplicated load-or-backup pattern
----------------------------------------------------------
The same try/except/move/print scaffold appeared in
`setup_onboarding_bypass` and `setup_claude_settings`. Extracted to
`_load_json_or_backup(path) -> tuple[dict, str]` returning a status
tag (`"loaded"`, `"absent"`, `"backed_up"`, `"failed"`). Each caller
inspects the tag — onboarding only proceeds on `"loaded"` (C2 fix);
settings proceeds on anything except `"failed"` (preserving original
intent of overwriting a missing/corrupt-then-backed-up file with
defaults).

LAT2 (review 2026-04-27) — `fix_directory_ownership` hardcodes
~/.claude instead of CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR
--------------------------------------------------------------
Latent today (devcontainer.json sets CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR to
/home/vscode/.claude, which equals `~/.claude`), but a user who points
the env var elsewhere would have ownership-fix skip the actual
directory. Mirror the pattern already used at the top of
`setup_claude_settings` so the two stay aligned.

Verification
============
The C1 quoting was verified live via a Python harness driving real
`git config --file --get` against a generated config: `Test #1 User`,
`j@x;y.com`, `Test "Q" Sir`, `path\\to\\file`, `  spaced  `, and
`Mr. O'Brien` all round-trip losslessly.

How to apply
============
From a shell on the host (NOT inside the devcontainer):

  cd <smudge repo root>
  git apply paad/code-reviews/deferred/2026-04-27-post_install-correctness-and-hardening.patch
  git add .devcontainer/post_install.py
  git commit -m "fix(devcontainer): post_install round-trip escaping + ordering + helpers (C1, C2, I2, I4, S1, S2, S4, LAT2)"

Then push.

