+def _backup_path(path: Path) -> Path:
+    """S1 (review 2026-04-27): timestamp-suffixed backup name.
+
+    `path.with_suffix(path.suffix + ".bak")` overwrites a prior backup
+    if one exists, destroying the older corrupt state and removing
+    forensic evidence. Suffix with epoch seconds so each failure keeps
+    its own backup. Within-second collisions on the same path are rare
+    enough to accept; the alternative (microsecond resolution) makes
+    the filename unwieldy without protecting any real recovery case.
